                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/27.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Sharp</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>452. Mr. Herrick’s despatch 767, November 17. Ask release Chandeysson, now in
                    120th French Territorials, and permission immediate return this country.
                    Department informed important interests here need his attention. See
                    Department’s telegram December 31 concerning August Peralme.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
